28:57.500 --> 29:00.173
The scent of the forest
after the spring rain.

29:00.900 --> 29:03.368
We imagine the path
underneath our feet.

29:04.140 --> 29:08.418
We see the green moist color
surrounding us.

29:09.100 --> 29:13.730
And we feel the wet branches
against our faces.

29:16.980 --> 29:18.971
And now imagine...

29:19.740 --> 29:21.696
- Oh...
- We pass between the trees.

29:21.740 --> 29:24.334
- I'm not going on my own. Come on.
- Oh, no.

29:24.420 --> 29:26.888
And we begin drawing in the air.

29:26.940 --> 29:29.010
Deep inside.

29:29.060 --> 29:31.255
And enjoy the moment.

29:35.340 --> 29:37.535
The humidity level is high.

29:37.580 --> 29:39.093
[plays dramatic tune]

29:44.340 --> 29:49.892
At the lower end there is the moss,
the fungi, the rotten leaves.

29:55.580 --> 29:59.175
The middle tone is the tall, fresh grass.

29:59.860 --> 30:02.579
A crisp and almost invigorating scent.

30:03.380 --> 30:05.371
[plucks high notes]

30:06.300 --> 30:10.009
And at the top we feel
not only the leaves and the rainwater,

30:10.060 --> 30:12.051
but also the sky.

30:12.100 --> 30:13.852
[high, ringing note]

30:13.980 --> 30:18.292
On a day like this...
we can smell the sky itself.

30:20.180 --> 30:22.171
