It's not true! Don't say that!
You're not on your own!

41:13.980 --> 41:15.971
You're not on your own!

41:16.060 --> 41:19.370
All your body, it turns...
it turns to fucking soup.

41:19.420 --> 41:20.614
First the terror.

41:20.660 --> 41:23.732
Don't leave me. Don't leave me, Michael.

41:23.780 --> 41:25.816
Don't leave me.

41:27.860 --> 41:29.896
And then a moment of hunger.

41:29.940 --> 41:31.931
Oh, my God. What's happened?

41:32.900 --> 41:35.619
Oh, my God, what's happened?
What's happening?

42:16.140 --> 42:18.131
[horn blares]

43:24.140 --> 43:26.176
[groans]

43:56.220 --> 43:59.451
This is how the sense of taste
disappears from our world.

44:05.460 --> 44:08.372
They don't even have time
to give the disease a name.

44:09.620 --> 44:11.611
[dog barks in distance]

44:35.700 --> 44:38.260
Do you think
we'll lose our other senses too?

44:41.940 --> 44:43.931
Smell and taste are related.

44:43.980 --> 44:46.016
They're the two chemical senses.

44:47.220 --> 44:49.609
So the other ones
might be all right, then?

44:50.540 --> 44:52.258
They might.

44:52.260 --> 44:54.296
Just have to wait and see.

44:55.300 --> 44:57.291
That's right, sailor.

45:03.660 --> 45:05.651
And what happens if you're wrong?

45:13.100 --> 45:15.136
[whispers]:
Then we're fucked.

47:00.380 --> 47:01.972
Hey.

47:02.020 --> 47:03.692
Hi.

47:05.180 --> 47:07.171
It's still out there.

47:08.260 --> 47:10.251
