47:10.300 --> 47:12.291
The world.

47:13.820 --> 47:15.811
What can you see?

47:15.900 --> 47:17.777
People.

47:17.820 --> 47:19.811
What are they doing?

47:20.740 --> 47:22.731
They're heading off to work.

47:26.500 --> 47:28.491
What should we do?

47:31.820 --> 47:33.811
We go to work as well.

47:37.900 --> 47:39.891
Do we kiss each other first...

47:41.820 --> 47:43.378
Maybe.

47:45.620 --> 47:47.850
..Say we'd like to see each other again?

47:49.380 --> 47:51.371
We probably do.

47:51.420 --> 47:53.411
Maybe even this evening.

48:00.340 --> 48:01.409
Maybe.

48:03.860 --> 48:05.851
And are we looking forward to that?

48:07.340 --> 48:08.489
Yes!

48:17.180 --> 48:19.171
I may not even have a job any more.

48:24.300 --> 48:27.098
Forget it, Michael, we're closed.
We're closed.

48:27.140 --> 48:29.131
We'll open again.

48:29.180 --> 48:31.296
People can't smell, they can't taste.

48:32.980 --> 48:34.971
They're going to buy flour and fat.

48:35.660 --> 48:37.651
That's all you need to survive.

48:39.300 --> 48:41.291
Take a hit on that. Go on. Go on.

48:42.340 --> 48:43.773
Drink that.

48:43.820 --> 48:45.890
Now, that is damned expensive brandy.

48:45.980 --> 48:47.891
Damned, damned expensive.

48:47.980 --> 48:51.177
But you might as well
drink surgical spirit or sniff glue.

48:51.220 --> 48:53.211
It doesn't matter.

48:53.260 --> 48:54.773
Flour and fat.

48:54.820 --> 48:57.175
- And yet it does matter.
- There's no difference.

48:57.220 --> 48:58.858
No, I think you're wrong.

48:59.580 --> 49:01.252
Life goes on.

49:05.780 --> 49:07.179
[exhales heavily]

49:08.180 --> 49:09.932
They'll come back.

49:09.980 --> 49:12.130
People will ask each other
out to dinner again.

49:12.180 --> 49:14.899
They'll toast each other
while we take care of their needs.

49:14.940 --> 49:18.694
- Yeah, and serve them flour and fat.
- No, anything but flour and fat.

49:25.180 --> 49:26.818
We'll be all right.

49:49.180 --> 49:53.253
